            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#sprecherM" start="931.059" end="x">Rolling, rolling. To roll [now it is clear] means, to turn like a tree [log] is being turned. That is how we had to 'cower'. Now, there was something interesting in that 'cowering'. It was fortunate for a Jew if he had a chance to die soon. But there were a lot of 'falling' people who suffered a day or two until they died. In order that these people could get a little bit more air, we usually placed them near the door, because through the cracks in the door these gravely ill people could get a little bit more air.</span>
