            <span class="who">
                <span class="">Max Sprecher</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#sprecherM" start="2176.792" end="x">We remained there at that time in insulation only for a short time, since September 1939 until the eight of January, 1940. On that day marched in a contingent or company of three hundred Jewish prisoners, for the brick factory. With that instant started the hardest and from certain aspects an easier period of our life in the <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a>. Harder, because we were transferred as a hard labor contingent, [assigned] to hardest labor with insufficient nourishment.</span>
