            <span class="utterance" who="#boderD" start="2296.204" end="x">[This is a rare case when the interviewer made an effort to redirect the interview. The reason if I remember correctly was the pressure of time under which I worked in Germany and the impatience, at times, of other interviewees who waited outside for their turn. In retrospect this appears unsatisfactory. It would have been better to let him talk in his chosen sequence and then stop the interview in the middle. But this might have evoked some protest and dissatisfaction. However, there are not too many of such 'redirected' interviews, at least not to such a degree. —D.P.B.] Let us now conclude with <a class="placename" href="#vothC99" type="camp">Sachsenhausen</a>, where did you go from <a class="placename" href="#vothC99" type="camp">Sachsenhausen</a>?</span>
