            <span class="utterance" who="#sprecherM" start="2846.965" end="x">In the course of that time I became so depleted of bodily strength that I was not able any more to execute the smallest, lightest tasks. I was then sent to the hospital [in] <a class="placename" href="#vothC4" type="camp">Auschwitz</a>. Usually the prisoners who were sent to the hospital <a class="placename" href="#vothC4" type="camp">Auschwitz</a>, would go at the next selection, at the next transport concentration into the crematories <a class="placename" href="#vothC4" type="camp">Auschwitz</a>- <a class="placename" href="#vothC10" type="camp">Birkenau</a>. I found out that a transport is to be assembled within the next few days, and I got out of the hospital.</span>
